    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>W.T.O. RULES AGAINST U.S.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elizabeth Olson</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Olson, Elizabeth</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>World Trade Organization panel upholds ruling requiring US to change a 1916 law that penalizes foreign companies for dumping low-priced goods on American market (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A World Trade Organization panel has upheld an earlier ruling requiring the United States to change an 84-year-old law that penalizes foreign companies for dumping low-priced goods on its markets. Two years ago, the European Union and Japan challenged the 1916 Anti-Dumping Act. A three-judge panel rebuffed United States government arguments that the law was rarely used and had never led to such penalties. The United States has until Oct. 1 to respond to the ruling.</p>
        <p>Elizabeth Olson</p>
      </block>
